solution.p:
(a)
The average value of radius has three significant digits, which we will use to round off crcumference and area. From using the average value of the radius we get

	 C \amp= 2\pi r = 2\times \pi \times 3.55 = 22.3\,\text{cm}\ \ \text{(rounded off!)}
	 A \amp= \pi r^2 = 39.6\,\text{cm}^2\ \  \text{(rounded off!)}
